1
00:01:14,800 --> 00:01:15,640
Captain.

2
00:01:16,360 --> 00:01:17,760
I may not have achievements,

3
00:01:17,760 --> 00:01:19,020
but I have worked hard.

4
00:01:19,840 --> 00:01:21,039
These past few days,

5
00:01:21,160 --> 00:01:22,800
haven't we just uncovered another

6
00:01:22,800 --> 00:01:24,640
Underground Party radio station?

7
00:01:24,640 --> 00:01:27,170
And executed two Underground Party members.

8
00:01:27,720 --> 00:01:29,120
I share the same

9
00:01:29,440 --> 00:01:30,840
mind and heart with you.

10
00:01:31,320 --> 00:01:32,039
We coexist

11
00:01:32,680 --> 00:01:33,940
and prosper together.

12
00:01:39,360 --> 00:01:40,280
Yes, Captain.

13
00:01:41,080 --> 00:01:42,880
For this case, the brothers in our Secret Service

14
00:01:42,880 --> 00:01:44,440
haven't slept for days.

15
00:01:45,320 --> 00:01:46,560
Look at Section Chief Qian,

16
00:01:46,560 --> 00:01:47,960
he's lost a lot of weight.

17
00:01:48,160 --> 00:01:49,490
Give us another chance.

18
00:01:52,920 --> 00:01:53,600
Okay.

19
00:01:54,560 --> 00:01:56,220
I'll give you one more chance.

20
00:02:00,720 --> 00:02:03,380
I guarantee the task will be completed in 3 days.

21
00:02:06,440 --> 00:02:07,970
How can you guarantee that?

22
00:02:13,040 --> 00:02:14,600
I guarantee it with my life.

23
00:02:16,520 --> 00:02:17,480
Look after

24
00:02:18,400 --> 00:02:19,440
your own head.

25
00:02:34,720 --> 00:02:35,840
Three days?

26
00:02:36,240 --> 00:02:37,570
It's extremely urgent!

27
00:02:46,920 --> 00:02:47,640
Chief,

28
00:02:47,840 --> 00:02:48,760
pacing around and worrying

29
00:02:48,760 --> 00:02:50,400
won't help.

30
00:02:56,120 --> 00:02:57,240
A few days ago,

31
00:02:57,600 --> 00:02:58,360
on the phone,

32
00:02:58,520 --> 00:03:00,520
your brother said there'd be news soon.

33
00:03:00,520 --> 00:03:02,050
Why is there still nothing?

34
00:03:02,640 --> 00:03:03,960
You know how my brother

35
00:03:03,960 --> 00:03:05,040
does things.

36
00:03:05,240 --> 00:03:06,120
He wouldn't promise you

37
00:03:06,120 --> 00:03:07,240
if he wasn't sure.

38
00:03:07,480 --> 00:03:09,560
I'll call him later and ask again.

39
00:03:10,840 --> 00:03:11,800
Hurry him up.

40
00:03:12,240 --> 00:03:12,960
Okay.

41
00:03:15,120 --> 00:03:16,079
No matter what,

42
00:03:16,760 --> 00:03:18,880
I can't let Matsuda chop my head off.

43
00:03:25,160 --> 00:03:25,800
Brother.

44
00:03:26,120 --> 00:03:28,000
We can't keep Qian Yugui around anymore.

45
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:29,360
He says everything is fine.

46
00:03:29,360 --> 00:03:31,360
But if he keeps following Lin Heming's lead,

47
00:03:31,360 --> 00:03:33,290
he will soon trace it back to Qin Na.

48
00:03:33,440 --> 00:03:35,300
Then Lingzi will be in danger too.

49
00:03:35,880 --> 00:03:36,680
Mr. Chen.

50
00:03:38,120 --> 00:03:39,000
I heard

51
00:03:39,480 --> 00:03:41,940
the president of Shunfa Advertising Agency

52
00:03:42,800 --> 00:03:43,930
is named Lin Heming.

53
00:03:57,160 --> 00:03:59,079
He has some connection

54
00:03:59,400 --> 00:04:01,060
with Qin Na's harmonica club.

55
00:04:06,760 --> 00:04:08,000
I know about this.

56
00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:09,760
This Lin Heming

57
00:04:09,960 --> 00:04:13,040
was indeed the president of Shunfa Advertising Agency before.

58
00:04:13,040 --> 00:04:14,800
When the harmonica club was founded the year before last,

59
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:15,880
this guy liked the harmonica,

60
00:04:15,880 --> 00:04:18,040
so he invested some money in the club

61
00:04:18,200 --> 00:04:20,720
and took a nominal position as vice president.

62
00:04:20,720 --> 00:04:22,079
Last month he transferred the advertising agency

63
00:04:22,079 --> 00:04:23,160
to Gao Ziying,

64
00:04:23,400 --> 00:04:24,200
left Harbin,

65
00:04:24,280 --> 00:04:26,210
and went to Shanghai for business.

66
00:04:29,400 --> 00:04:30,600
What's wrong, Chief?

67
00:04:30,880 --> 00:04:31,600
Nothing.

68
00:04:31,760 --> 00:04:32,800
I was just asking.

69
00:04:33,520 --> 00:04:34,400
Chief Qian?

70
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:36,040
This is Shen Yan.

71
00:04:38,200 --> 00:04:38,880
Chief Qian,

72
00:04:39,520 --> 00:04:41,850
President Wang has news about the killer.

73
00:04:42,680 --> 00:04:43,640
In half an hour,

74
00:04:44,040 --> 00:04:46,040
at the Blues Cafe on Central Street.

75
00:04:46,240 --> 00:04:47,240
I'll wait for you.

76
00:04:47,560 --> 00:04:48,960
Don't wear your uniform.

77
00:05:00,760 --> 00:05:01,680
Two of you stay here.

78
00:05:01,680 --> 00:05:02,940
Two of you come with me.

79
00:05:10,880 --> 00:05:11,600
Mr. Shen.

80
00:05:12,040 --> 00:05:12,720
Chief Qian.

81
00:05:12,960 --> 00:05:13,640
Have a seat.

82
00:05:14,720 --> 00:05:15,880
What would you like to drink?

83
00:05:15,880 --> 00:05:16,760
No, thanks.

84
00:05:17,040 --> 00:05:17,760
By the way,

85
00:05:18,120 --> 00:05:20,120
President Wang has news.

86
00:05:21,200 --> 00:05:21,960
Yes.

87
00:05:25,520 --> 00:05:26,200
Mr. Shen,

88
00:05:26,360 --> 00:05:27,960
this is timely help.

89
00:05:29,160 --> 00:05:30,640
How is it timely help?

90
00:05:31,240 --> 00:05:32,000
Chief Qian,

91
00:05:32,920 --> 00:05:35,320
I am putting the icing on the cake for you.

92
00:05:36,480 --> 00:05:37,680
Icing on the cake?

93
00:05:38,560 --> 00:05:39,240
What

94
00:05:39,400 --> 00:05:40,480
does that mean?

95
00:05:41,080 --> 00:05:42,200
You are now

96
00:05:42,200 --> 00:05:44,060
an influential figure in Harbin.

97
00:05:47,600 --> 00:05:48,640
I heard

98
00:05:48,960 --> 00:05:50,560
your wife beat up a Japanese.

99
00:05:50,600 --> 00:05:51,560
Impressive.

100
00:05:53,760 --> 00:05:55,800
No, no.

101
00:05:57,320 --> 00:05:58,320
It was just

102
00:05:58,520 --> 00:06:00,560
a little friction.

103
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:03,040
The Japanese are particular.

104
00:06:03,040 --> 00:06:04,040
They do things

105
00:06:04,480 --> 00:06:05,120
fairly.

106
00:06:05,200 --> 00:06:05,920
Really?

107
00:06:06,360 --> 00:06:07,620
Tell me what happened.

108
00:06:08,960 --> 00:06:09,760
Mr. Shen,

109
00:06:09,960 --> 00:06:12,120
let's talk about it another day.

110
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:16,320
What did President Wang say?

111
00:06:25,120 --> 00:06:27,180
All the information about the killer

112
00:06:27,320 --> 00:06:28,080
is here.

113
00:06:28,240 --> 00:06:29,570
President Wang gave it.

114
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:34,640
Read it after I leave.

115
00:06:34,840 --> 00:06:36,440
I know nothing about this.

116
00:06:40,760 --> 00:06:42,640
It's all your credit.

117
00:06:43,880 --> 00:06:44,760
How particular.

118
00:06:44,760 --> 00:06:46,800
Mr. Shen is particular. I will see you out.

119
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:47,800
Let me see you out.

120
00:06:48,840 --> 00:06:49,800
Please, no need to see me out.

121
00:06:49,800 --> 00:06:51,240
Alright. Take care.

122
00:06:51,320 --> 00:06:51,920
Okay.

123
00:07:10,720 --> 00:07:12,780
Section Chief Chen, why are you here?

124
00:07:21,240 --> 00:07:22,280
Don't bump into me.

125
00:07:22,280 --> 00:07:23,340
What are you doing?

126
00:09:02,440 --> 00:09:04,160
Brother, let's talk this out.

127
00:09:11,840 --> 00:09:13,640
What did the letter say just now?

128
00:09:16,200 --> 00:09:16,880
Mr. Shen.

129
00:09:17,080 --> 00:09:18,000
I am asking you.

130
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:21,530
The letter just now said

131
00:09:22,640 --> 00:09:23,440
the killer

132
00:09:25,040 --> 00:09:26,360
is right beside you.

133
00:09:29,440 --> 00:09:31,100
Then you'd better be careful.

134
00:09:48,240 --> 00:09:48,920
Reporting.

135
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:52,920
Reporting, Chief.

136
00:09:52,920 --> 00:09:57,120
Captain Li San of the plainclothes squad, recovered and returning to duty.

137
00:10:03,680 --> 00:10:04,810
You're discharged.

138
00:10:04,880 --> 00:10:06,600
Congratulations, Chief Chen.

139
00:10:06,600 --> 00:10:08,120
What's there to congratulate?

140
00:10:08,120 --> 00:10:09,650
We put our lives on the line.

141
00:10:10,760 --> 00:10:11,690
How's your head?

142
00:10:12,720 --> 00:10:13,850
It still hurts a bit,

143
00:10:14,080 --> 00:10:15,280
but it's much better.

144
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:17,120
Who was it?

145
00:10:17,400 --> 00:10:18,730
Hitting me from behind.

146
00:10:19,120 --> 00:10:20,520
And even took my gun.

147
00:10:21,640 --> 00:10:22,840
He's quite ruthless.

148
00:10:24,160 --> 00:10:25,420
Don't let me catch him.

149
00:10:25,760 --> 00:10:26,760
I'll kill him.

150
00:10:31,280 --> 00:10:32,160
Captain Li,

151
00:10:32,560 --> 00:10:34,240
since you've rejoined the team,

152
00:10:34,240 --> 00:10:36,160
you have to lead the plainclothes squad well.

153
00:10:36,160 --> 00:10:37,290
Yes, Section Chief.

154
00:10:37,720 --> 00:10:38,650
Get back to work.

155
00:11:01,480 --> 00:11:02,160
Uncle Li.

156
00:11:04,040 --> 00:11:05,280
Miss Qin, you're back.

157
00:11:05,280 --> 00:11:06,520
Just call me if you need anything.

158
00:11:06,520 --> 00:11:08,450
It's fine. Go ahead with your work.

159
00:11:37,200 --> 00:11:38,200
Mr. Matsuda.

160
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:41,200
What brings you here?

161
00:11:41,600 --> 00:11:42,400
Miss Qin.

162
00:11:42,760 --> 00:11:44,620
The concert is in a couple of days.

163
00:11:44,920 --> 00:11:46,780
How are your preparations going?

164
00:11:47,520 --> 00:11:48,720
Everything is ready.

165
00:11:48,720 --> 00:11:50,580
Please don't worry, Mr. Matsuda.

166
00:11:54,560 --> 00:11:57,440
It's too noisy around here.

167
00:11:57,960 --> 00:12:00,440
I want to move you to a quiet place

168
00:12:00,680 --> 00:12:01,840
to practice in peace.
